Kim Jong Il visits South Hamgyong Province 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the industrial field of South Hamgyong Province from Sept. 22 to 24.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   During the guidance he looked round the Sinhung Machinery Plant, the June 1 Youth General Electric Appliances Plant, the Hamhung Disabled Soldiers' Plastic Daily Necessities Plant, Songchongang Power Station no. 22, the Hamhung Songchongang Garment Factory, the Sinhung Fish Farm, the Sinhung Pleasure Ground and other factories and enterprises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the Sinhung Machinery Plant, he learned about the production of machines. He said the solid foundation of the powerful self-reliant industries enables the Koreans to manufacture any modern machine at will and that this is a clear demonstration of the validity and great vitality of the Worker's Party of Korea's line of building an independent national economy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At the June 1 Youth General Electric Appliances Plant, he went round production processes, highly praising the workers of the plant for having produced electric appliances in time needed for different domains during the "arduous march" and the forced march and greatly contributed to making the national economy Juche-oriented, modern and scientific. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He went to the Hamhung disabled soldiers' plastic daily necessities plant and the Hamhung Songchongang Garment Factory. At the plant, he showed warm loving care and favors for the disabled soldiers, saying that they are valuable treasures of the nation as they fought for the motherland and the people at the cost of blood and, therefore, they should be given best conditions for work, rest and life. He met with disabled soldiers and their wives, had a pep-talk with them and posed for a picture with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   At Songchongang Power Station no. 22, he looked round the inside, saying that when officials use their brains and organise the work well, they can tap a lot of potentials for electricity anywhere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He also visited the Sinhung fish farm and the Sinhung pleasure ground. He noted with great satisfaction that the county had done good things for the sake of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   After that, he gave important tasks to further develop the industries in the province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He highly praised the party members and other working people in the province for having done a lot of things in all domains including the normalization of production and the building of power stations by speeding up the grand march to build a powerful nation after their successful completion of the "arduous march" and the forced march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Great changes are taking place in every part of the province, resulting in miracles and innovations every day, he noted, adding that this is an expression of the indomitable will of the heroic Korean people who have withstood all trials of history and won victory after victory and a proud demonstration of the inexhaustible strength of the wholeheartedly united Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He said further development of the industries in the province is of great importance in developing the national economy as a whole because the province has extracting, power, chemical and many other key industries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He advanced concrete tasks to further develop the chemical and power industries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
  He urged the province to supply lots of delicious and nutritious fresh-water fishes to the people through extensive fish culture because the province has many areas with favorable conditions for fish culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He also called for building more pleasure grounds on the scenic seaside and mountains so that the working people can fully enjoy themselves and take a rest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He was accompanied by chief secretary of the south Hamgyong provincial committee of the Worker's Party of Korea Ri Thae Nam, chairman of the south Hamgyong provincial people's committee Kim Phung Gi, secretaries Jong Pyong Ho and Kim Kuk Thae and first vice department directors Pak Song Bong, Jang Song Thaek and Choe Chun Hwang of the WPK Central Committee.

Floral basket laid before statue of Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Chief Pak Kwang Gi and members of the Pyongyang mission of the National Democratic Front of South Korea laid a floral basket before the statue of the President Kim Il Sung on Mansu Hill on Friday on the occasion of the autumn festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They laid the floral basket before his statue and paid tribute to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   And they laid bouquets before the bust of Kim Jong Suk, the great communist revolutionary fighter, in the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong and observed a moment's silence in memory of her.

Korea's reunification supported by foreign presidents
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Presidents of many countries who were participating in the 54th session of the UN General Assembly met DPRK Foreign Minister Paek Nam Sun on September 20 and expressed their support for the cause of Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The Zimbabwean President hoped that the Korean people would register greater success in socialist construction under the leadership of the great Marshal Kim Jong Il and that Korea would be reunified at an early date on the basis of three principles of national reunification true to the behest of the great leader Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Algerian President said that he would support the DPRK according to his faith in the future, too, as in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The Namibian President said that Namibia and the DPRK have very good friendly relations and he would as ever fully support the Korean people's struggle for national reunification.

Wreaths at Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Leading officials of the party and the state, servicemen of the people's army and working people laid wreaths at the Revolutionary Martyrs' Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on Friday morning on the occasion of the harvest festival (Sept. 24). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A wreath sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il was laid on the wreath-laying stand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Hong Song Nam, Paek Hak Rim, Kim Il Chol, Kim Ki Nam and other officials of political parties, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, general officers and soldiers of the Korean People's Army and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They paid a silent tribute to communist revolutionary martyrs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Wreaths were also laid before the graves of Kim Po Hyon, Ri Po Ik, Kim Hyong Jik and Kang Pan Sok at the Mangyongdae Revolutionary Site, the Patriotic Martyrs' Cemetery and martyrs' statues, monuments to them and their graves in different areas.

Anti-social educational policy rejected
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- General student councils of over 50 universities including Korea University, Kyunghee University and Chungang University formed Anti-Registration Fees University Councils and rejected the authorities' anti-social educational policy, according to a report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Student representatives called a press conference at the student hall of Seoul National University to denounce the authorities for collecting tuition fees with membership fees unilaterally added to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   They clarified that in this regard they would send an open questionnaire to the ministry of education and hold a public hearing.

DPRK joint statement supported in Bangladesh
  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- The socialist party, the labour party and other political parties and organizations of Bangladesh issued a joint statement on September 18 in support of the September 10 joint statement of the political parties and public organizations of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It said that the U.S. hostile policy towards the DPRK poses a threat not only to the peace and stability of the Korean peninsula but also to world peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The U.S. and South Korean authorities should withdraw their "Northern Limit Line" immediately and stop their anti-DPRK moves at once. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We demand that the following three proposals put forward by the DPRK to establish a new peace mechanism be realised: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Firstly, agreeing on management and operation of the Military Demarcation Line and the demilitarized zone, secondly, organizing and operating a DPRK-U.S. joint military organization and thirdly, starting negotiations for the signing of a peace agreement between the DPRK and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   We urge the U.S. and the South Korean authorities to affirmatively respond to the magnanimous and peace-oriented proposals of the DPRK.

Senior party and state officials express condolences
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Senior party and state officials visited the bier of the late Ri Jong Ok, politburo member of the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea and Honorary Vice-President of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, and expressed condolences over his death on Sept. 23 and 24. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   A wreath sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il was standing by the bier. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   There were also wreaths from the Central Committee of the Worker's Party of Korea, the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Honor guards were standing by the sides of the bier. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Visitors included Kim Yong Nam, Jo Myong Rok Pak Song Chol and Hong Song Nam and other senior party and state officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Officials of the party, armed forces and power organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and people from all walks of life also expressed condolences over his death. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Overseas compatriots on visit to the socialist homeland, the diplomatic corps and the military attaches' corps here visited the Sojang Club where the bier of the deceased is placed and expressed condolences over his death.

Bellicose outburst of S. Korean "PM"
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Pil, "Prime Minister" of South Korea, at a "government"-sponsored function held on Wednesday ballyhooed about the "engagement policy towards the north" and in sheer vexation cried out for "establishing a perfect security posture to defeat" someone "in an emergency." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   What Kim Jong Pil has done over the last nearly four decades is nothing but selling off the country and the nation to outside forces, fascistizing South Korean society and laying obstacles in the way of the country's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   That day he raved about the "engagement policy" and unexpectedly made such bellicose outburst revealing his wild ambition for aggression on the north. This proves that the "engagement policy" on the lips of the present ruling quarters is just the other side of the policy for aggression against the north.

Peace on Korean peninsula demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- A resolution calling for establishing peace on the Korean peninsula was adopted at a recent session of the executive committee of the International League of Women for Peace and Freedom held in Costa Rica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Expressing apprehension as to the situation on the Korean peninsula where the state of division and confrontation persist, the resolution called for sincerely implementing the three principles--independence, peaceful reunification and great national unity--the principles clarified in the July 4 joint statement and respecting the "agreement on reconciliation, non-aggression, cooperation and exchange between the north and south."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
It demanded the U.S. stop its moves to establish "Theatre Missile Defense" system, nullify the up-to-dated "U.S.-Japan Defense Cooperation Guidelines", normalize the relations with the DPRK and replace the Armistice Agreement with a peace agreement.

Kim Jong Il's 5 years of ideological and theoretical activities

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il is a peerlessly great man who opened a new turning phase of the revolution through his extraordinary ideological and theoretical activities over the past five years, says Rodong Sinmun in a signed article today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is Kim Jong Il who wrought miracles in such adversities as the nation's greatest loss in its history spanning thousands of years, serious economic difficulties and consecutive years of natural calamities, the imperialists' heinous moves to isolate and stifle the DPRK in the wake of the collapse of socialism in different countries and their reactionary ideological offensive, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His ideological and theoretical activities over the past five years are characterized by his intense loyalty to hold the preceding leader in high esteem for all ages and the burning patriotic determination to build our country into a powerful socialist nation with the greatest vitality in all domains. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He put forward many ideological and theoretical policies to perpetuate the memory of the leader including the idea of upholding the President Kim Il Sung as the eternal leader of the Worker's Party of Korea and revolution, the eternal President of the DPRK, the idea of making all the people live and fight as befitting the soldiers and disciples of the leader and the policy of considering all the instructions given by the leader in his lifetime as his behest and carrying them through. As a result, the revolutionary theory of the working class on perpetuating the memory of the leader has been consummated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His steadfast will to faithfully carry forward the revolutionary idea of the President without the slightest deviation is fully reflected in his strong resolution that no change should be expected from him and in his works  including "on preserving the Juche character and national character of the revolution and construction."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He also set forth the army-first revolutionary idea which can confidently guarantee the building of a powerful nation and the idea of revitalizing the socialist economy, the idea of running at a canter on steed and many other ideas and policies based on an analysis of the realistic requirements of the developing Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   His ideological and theoretical activities are based on the noble mission to lead the destiny of humankind, the destiny of the overall socialist cause in a responsible manner. He clearly indicated the way of rebirth of the socialist movement and its final victory in many works including "socialism is a science."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   He could perform the great ideological and theoretical feats which will shine forever with the century over the past five years through his extraordinary ideological and theoretical activities as he has clairvoyant philosophical wisdom, superhuman extraordinary passion, a history of prolonged revolutionary activities and exceptionally rich experience of revolutionary leadership as the thinker and theoretician whom no one can match. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   It is the faith and courage of the Korean people that there are nothing to fear and no insurmountable obstacles before them as they are guided by his outstanding ideas and theories, despite manifold trials.

Greetings to Yemeni President 
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- President Kim Yong Nam of the presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK today sent a message of greetings to Ali Abdullah Saleh, President of Yemen, on the occasion of the 37th anniversary of the Yemeni Day of Revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   The message expressed belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would develop on good terms and wished the President and people of Yemen greater success in the work for the stability and the prosperity of the country.

Greetings exchanged
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 25 (KCNA) -- Paek Nam Sun, Foreign Minister of the DPRK, exchanged messages of greetings with Norris Charles, Minister of Foreign Affairs, Trade and Commerce of the Commonwealth of Dominica, on the occasion of the 20th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   Paek Nam Sun in his message expressed the belief that the friendly relations between the two countries would favorably develop in the future, too,  while  Norris Charles hoped that the friendly relations between the two countries will further develop in the mutual interests.
